I do much suspect that these three books laid up in the court answered to the threefold congregation of the Jews, namely, in J udea, Babylon, and Egypt, whence these copies might be particularly taken. For, however that nation was scattered abroad almost throughout the whole world, yet, by number and companies scarcely to be numbered, it more plentifully increased in these three countries than any where else: in Judea, by those that returned from Babylon; in Babylon, by those that returned not3 and in Egypt, by the temple of Onias.
